scripts.comment: Angles are a way to measure how much something turns. On the stage you can see a protractor, which is a device used to measure angles. Like a clock measures in seconds, and a ruler measures in centimeters, angles are measured in degrees. One full rotation is 360 degrees!
Click to turn the sprite 15 degrees at a time. A square corner is 90 degrees. Try changing the number around.
